outline:
1. priest, principal officer or chief ruler
    1. priest-king (Melchizedek, Messiah)
    2. pagan priests
    3. priests of Jehovah
    4. Levitical priests
    5. Zadokite priests
    6. Aaronic priests
    7. the high priest
kjv_def: chief ruler, [idiom] own, priest, prince, principal officer.
strongs_def: literally one officiating, a priest; also (by courtesy) an acting priest (although a layman)
